name: Florida
main_font: Narrow sans serif, proprietary variant of Highway Gothic
main_plate_text: "Florida" at top, county name/"Sunshine State"/"In God We Trust" at bottom

sticker_format.color: Retroreflective material as specified by DHSMV
sticker_format.position: Upper right corner of license plate
sticker_format.description: Validation sticker shows month, license plate number, and year of expiration. Treated with retroreflective material per statute.

notes: Florida comprehensive implementation with 292 official plate types from DMV matrix data (Jun 25, 2024). CRITICAL: Does NOT use letter 'O' - only zero '0'. Font changes in 2008 & 2019. Primary toll reading state with extensive specialty plate program requiring accurate identification. Includes ALL processing metadata: prefix/suffix rules, numeric validation, visual identifiers, vehicle type identification. Does not use letter 'O' on standard plates. Always use zero '0'.

processing_metadata.description: Official Florida DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.no_letter_o: Does not use the Letter 'O', we only use the number zero '0'. If the letter 'O' is entered it automatically changes to zero '0' in our motor vehicle database.
global_rules.code_system: Florida uses Plate Type Code numbers to apply proper prefix/suffix currently. The only plate type code used is Passenger Plate Default: 0
